    "Given the distinct pretraining paradigms of vision encoders (contrastive learning (Radford et al., 2021) and self-supervised learning (Oquab et al., 2024)), the feature quality assessment differs accordingly: for contrastivetrained encoders, the corresponding text encoder enables zero-shot analysis, while for supervisedtrained ones, linear probing (Alain and Bengio, 2018) and clustering analysis serve to assess their extracted features.",
